{"key":"processedPost-13727557","value":{"id":13727557,"first":13726722,"last":13730210,"when":1294125155,"utime":"01/04/11 09:12 AM","cleanedPost":"You need to mist.&nbsp; <br />It's extremely important for moisture to be evaporating from the substrate, as this is the number 1 pinning trigger.&nbsp; If you saturate your substrates, they'll perform poorly.&nbsp; You want moisture to leave the casing or substrate/cake, etc., and then you replace it with misting.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of substrate moisture is what makes mushrooms pop.<br />Everyone in a cold climate should run a humidifier or two in their house all winter while running the heat.&nbsp; We keep a large kettle of water boiling on the wood stove all winter.<br />RR"}}